On Mon, 20 Dec 1999, Bernhard Rosenkraenzer wrote:
> The printer seems to have a problem switching to IEEE1284_DEVICEID mode
> shortly after initialization.
This is quite believable: it gets reset when parport_pc loads, and it
might be a bit dazed for a short time afterward.
> It happens in userspace, too, if the program accessing /dev/parport0 has
> to autoload the module.
What exactly is getting autoloaded -- the whole parport stack?  Can you
see how long after parport_pc loads you have to wait before things are
okay again?  Put a post-install parport_pc rule in modules.conf to sleep
for varying numbers of seconds.
Thanks,
Tim.
